              <h2>Frequently asked questions about Mississippi income tax</h2>

              <h3>Is Mississippi really eliminating its income tax?</h3>
              <p>
                Mississippi has enacted legislation to
                <strong>phase down</strong> the income tax and has removed the
                lowest brackets, moving toward a lower flat rate. Whether the
                tax is fully eliminated will depend on future revenue
                performance and additional laws passed by the legislature and
                signed by the governor.
              </p>

              <h3>
                Does Mississippi tax Social Security or retirement income?
              </h3>
              <p>
                Mississippi generally
                <strong>does not tax Social Security benefits</strong> and
                provides broad exemptions for many types of retirement income
                (such as qualified pensions and IRAs) for residents. However,
                rules can be nuanced, so retirees should confirm details with
                the
                <a
                  href="https://www.dor.ms.gov/individual"
